DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260419T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260419T230000
SUMMARY:Passaic Watershed Mountain and Valley Hike
DESCRIPTION:Metrotrails: NJ\, PA\, NY Metropolitan Area Hiking and More!\n
 Join us for a very happy loop hike\, more in our Passaic River series\, bu
 t this time filling in some gaps of interesting places we missed on previo
 us trips\, and featuring Garrett Mountain and Rifle Camp Park this time!\n
 We will meet at 9 am at West Falls Plaza\, which we've used a couple of ti
 mes\, and make our way to the Passaic River. This time\, we'll cross the r
 iver and follow a road upstream on the opposite side we did last time.\nWe
 'll get off of the road and walk through Laurel Grove and Mt Nebo Cemeteri
 es\, and then Holy Sepulchre Cemetery after a few blocks of road walk.\nWe
  will then take the West Side Park trails and Riverside Terrace to the eas
 t for a bit. This will lead us around the Great Falls again covering a cou
 ple of different trails from before. We then come up past the Reservoir\, 
 cross Rt 80 at New Street\, and head up into Garrett Mountain Park. We'll 
 make our way through there\, and loop in a roundabout way through that par
 k south to Rifle Camp Park. We'll loop from the east side of that as far s
 outh as we can\, then back to the north on the west side. This will then t
 ake us back to Garrett Mountain\, and we'll descend west though Zekeriah P
 ark.\nA few blocks on the road takes us through Diane Grimes Park\, then a
  bit more to the Morris Canal Greenway. We will loop back to where we star
 ted from here to close this very diverse 15 mile loop.\nIf needed\, contac
 t me at 908 343 8374
